Package: smplMath
Type: Package
Title: Returns Data Relations per Variable and Generates Separate Visualization on Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: "Sherman LaCost [aut, cre]"
Maintainer: The package maintainer <sherman.b.lacost@gmail.com> 
Description: Simple to use package to compute and see if your data positively or negatively related,
    can generate visualizations based on provided data up to 3 or 4 values/columns. Supposed to simplify the process
    of quick and simple visualizations as well as basic analytics just by inputing data
Depends: ggplot2, dplyr, e1071, caret, kernlab
License: CCO
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
